HEADWORD: Horography
<hw>Ho*rog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ hour +
<ets>-graphy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>horographie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An account of the hours.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of constructing instruments for making the
hours, as clocks, watches, and dials.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horologe</ent>⟦br⟧
